                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13593815" author="brandon.williams" created="Tue, 5 Mar 2013 19:40:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is a pernicious thing to debug, since the timing condition is so tight; enabling DEBUG or TRACE even on just the gossiper does not let it reproduce.  However, careful examination of the INFO messages tells us that handleMajorStateChange is not being called since there is no &apos;node restarted&apos; message, which means applyStateLocally is the only other option, and that is called in the ack/ack2 handlers. This tells us that we&apos;re in the middle of a gossip round when we send the shutdown message, so the easiest thing to do is sleep for more than one round.  Trivial patch to do so, which has solved this on the dtests.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13594364" author="vijay2win@yahoo.com" created="Wed, 6 Mar 2013 04:51:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13595068" author="brandon.williams" created="Wed, 6 Mar 2013 20:28:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;v2 adds just a touch more protection and ignores ack2 when gossip is disabled, which we were already doing in ack/syn.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13595151" author="jasobrown" created="Wed, 6 Mar 2013 21:48:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 on v2&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13595178" author="brandon.williams" created="Wed, 6 Mar 2013 22:10:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
